# Polite Refuser — House #3 Jewish, v1.
#
# M4.6 structural skeleton + M4.6 Phase 4 dialogue subagent content pass.
# Voice profile: cast.md § 6.0.3 — EMPATHY-BAR RED LINES APPLY (see the
# RED-LINE COMPLIANCE STATEMENT block below + dialogue-context.md § 8
# "trust the player to notice").
#
# Topology mirrors polite_refuser_house05_catholic_v1.dtl. Outcome signals
# identical. Mid-conversation exit (ESC / Walk-away) → REFUSED (door-side).
# arc_state branching via top-level if/else + jump/label.
# Character slug: polite_refuser_house03_jewish.
#
# Character interpretation (Phase 4 subagent, M4.6+):
# Suburban American woman, mid-50s, married, professional, long-time
# neighborhood resident. Cultural-and-possibly-religious Jew — High
# Holidays maybe, weekly synagogue not assumed. The "we" in her lines
# is the household (she + spouse; kids grown). Jewish identity
# integrated into normal life — a mezuzah on the doorframe, not a
# debating posture. Voice DNA = brevity-as-weight: direct, no
# stutter, warm-but-firm. The brevity differentiates from Catholic
# (verbal-rich stutter), Episcopalian (gracious-practiced warmth),
# and atheist (flat short). Warmth lives in firmness, not in volume.
#
# Phase 1 locks (Andrew, M4.6 Phase 4 session):
# - Q1a: woman, mid-50s, married, professional
# - Q1b: mezuzah → inline scene-note (preserves design intent for
#   future portrait/background pass)
# - Q1c: Lighthouse-glance → inline scene-note (captures the
#   "pause registered, nothing said" beat without structural
#   portrait change)
# - Q1d: defensible across all 4 prior outcomes (arc_state binary;
#   STATUS L351-354)
#
# Phase 0 silent-decision resolutions:
# - Returning E1 stutter → ABSENT. No "Oh —" stumble. Differentiator
#   from Catholic / Episcopalian / atheist returning E1s, all of
#   which share the "Oh —" PR-DNA. Per cast.md § 6.0.3 "warmth lives
#   in firmness, not in volume."
# - First_visit E3b tract acceptance → RELUCTANT-POLITE ("Alright.
#   Thank you."). Topology routes via TRACT_LEFT signal arg despite
#   cast.md LOW probability flag; UNSURE annotated.
# - Returning E3d compression → drop "just", keep "Sorry" ("It
#   isn't. Sorry."). Politeness anchor preserved per no-confrontation
#   red line; "just" dropped per skeleton "even shorter than first
#   visit."
# - Off-script publisher choice text "Why is that for you?" KEPT
#   verbatim; OFFSCRIPT_CHOICE_TEXTS dict unchanged. Jewish voice
#   brevity-as-weight lands in the HOUSEHOLDER response (E3d), not
#   the publisher choice.
#
# RED-LINE COMPLIANCE STATEMENT (cast.md § 6.0.3 internalized):
# Zero WWII / Holocaust references anywhere in this file. Zero
# "your people" or "we know what your organization teaches" beats.
# No stage-Jewish accent. No performed-tolerance framing. The
# historical weight is the player's; the dialogue trusts the player
# to carry it.

if TerritoryManager.pending_arc_state() == "first_visit":
	jump first_visit
else:
	jump returning

label first_visit

join polite_refuser_house03_jewish (neutral) at center

# Scene note: a small mezuzah is visible on the doorframe —
# publisher's brain registers, does not name. Future portrait
# pass / door_knock background-art: render via doorframe detail.
# Cast.md § 6.0.3 "Jewish identity integrated into normal life."

Good morning. We're sharing a brief encouraging message from the Bible today.
update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (polite_smile)
polite_refuser_house03_jewish (polite_smile): Good morning.

# Scene note: her eyes flick briefly to the public Lighthouse in
# the publisher's hand — pause registered, nothing said. Cast.md
# § 6.0.3 "may glance at the visible Lighthouse magazine ... pause
# registered, then nothing said."
#
# UNSURE: the recognition beat lives ONLY in this scene-note today;
# the structural portrait sequence is neutral → polite_smile with
# no awkward_pause beat. If playtest reads as missing the pause-
# registered moment, the fix is a structural portrait change — insert
# "update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (awkward_pause)" between the
# publisher pitch and the E1 line — deferred to a future per-
# character portrait pass.
polite_refuser_house03_jewish (polite_smile): I appreciate it, but we're Jewish.

- Of course, we respect that.
	update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief)
	polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief): Thank you. Have a good day.
	[signal arg="REFUSED"]
	[end_timeline]
- May I leave this with you anyway?
	update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (awkward_pause)
	# UNSURE: topology forces TRACT_LEFT via signal arg despite cast.md § 6.0.3
	# noting "many Jewish households decline JW literature on principle without
	# explaining why." Written as reluctant-polite acceptance ("Alright. Thank
	# you."). If playtest reads as out-of-character, a topology-extension
	# milestone could route this branch to REFUSED — structural, deferred.
	polite_refuser_house03_jewish (awkward_pause): Alright. Thank you.
	update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief)
	polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief): Have a good day.
	[signal arg="TRACT_LEFT"]
	[end_timeline]
- Could I come back another time?
	update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (awkward_pause)
	polite_refuser_house03_jewish (awkward_pause): I don't think so. But thank you.
	- I'll come back Tuesday.
		update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief)
		polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief): Alright. Tuesday.
		[signal arg="RETURN_VISIT_SCHEDULED"]
		[end_timeline]
	- Sounds good, take care.
		update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief)
		polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief): Thank you. Take care.
		[signal arg="REFUSED"]
		[end_timeline]
- Why is that for you? | [if DoubtMeter.value >= 25] [else=disable alt_text=""]
	update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (firm_refusal)
	polite_refuser_house03_jewish (firm_refusal): It just isn't. Sorry.
	update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (polite_smile)
	polite_refuser_house03_jewish (polite_smile): Was there anything else?
	- I'm sorry, that was forward of me.
		update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief)
		polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief): It's alright. Have a good day.
		[signal arg="REFUSED"]
		[end_timeline]
	- May I leave this with you?
		update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (awkward_pause)
		polite_refuser_house03_jewish (awkward_pause): Alright. Thank you.
		update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief)
		polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief): Have a good day.
		[signal arg="TRACT_LEFT"]
		[end_timeline]

label returning

join polite_refuser_house03_jewish (neutral) at center

Good morning. We were in the neighborhood again.
update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (polite_smile)
polite_refuser_house03_jewish (polite_smile): Hello again.

# UNSURE: "as I think I said" memory callback mirrors Catholic-returning's
# "like I said" gambit. Reads cleanly on long-interval re-knocks (1+ weeks
# per arc_state binary minimum interval; STATUS L355-356). On close-interval
# returns could read as mildly chiding. If close-interval playtest reads as
# scold, swap to "We're Jewish, thank you." (drops the memory callback).
polite_refuser_house03_jewish (polite_smile): We're Jewish — as I think I said.

- Of course, we won't keep you.
	update polite_refuser_house03_jewish (relief)
